fields.value: Supplemental Data from: Pankey et al., 2014

dsDescriptionValue.value: Alignments, phylogeny, character data, transcriptomes and read counts used for published analyses of bioluminescent organ evolution in cephalopods Uroteuthis edulis and Euprymna scolopes. Raw data available through NCBI SRA BioProject PRJNA257113.

publicationCitation.value: Pankey MS, Minin VN, Imholte GC, Suchard MA, Oakley TH (2014) Predictable transcriptome evolution in the convergent and complex bioluminescent organs of squid. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences 111 (44) E4736â€“E4742. doi: 10.1073/pnas.1416574111

files.description: Illumina reads from each library were mapped to the organism's collective Trinity-assembled transcriptome. All transcriptomes from each species were pooled and clustered to 90% similarity. Orthologous transcripts between species were estimated by best reciprocal BLAST match. Counts were aggregated from original transcripts belonging to each ortholog.
files.label: alllibs90.blastn.counts.tab

files.description: Illumina reads from each library were mapped to the organism's collective Trinity-assembled transcriptome using RSEM. All transcriptomes from each species were pooled and clustered to 90% similarity. Orthologous transcripts between species and the UniProt90 reference database were estimated by best reciprocal BLAST match. Counts were aggregated from original transcripts belonging to each UniProt match.
files.label: alllibs90.blastn.uniprotID.counts.tab
